Meanwhile, thousands of Jewish settlers and their right-wing supporters are
protesting for a second straight day in southern Israel against the mid-August
Gaza evacuation.
The protesters, encamped near the Israeli border town of Ofakim, have vowed to
march to nearby Gaza later Wednesday, despite Israeli warnings that 15,000
police deployed in the area will stop them.
Israel closed Gaza to all Israeli non-residents last month, and police and
troops have blocked earlier attempts by protesters to enter the territory.
